declare the new class in the profile with and ID of &quot;seeds&quot;:



&lt;bean id=
=3D&quot;seeds&quot; class=3D&quot;uk.bl.wap.modules.seeds.DbSeedModule&quot;&gt;

&lt;property name=
=3D&quot;...&quot;/&gt;

                ...

&lt;/bean&gt;



It calls an external SOAP proc=
ess which returns an ArrayList&lt;String&gt;,
each of which is converted to a Cra=
wlURI and then passed to
publishAddedSeed(). Presumably you could do someth=
ing similar via JDBC.



Not sure if this is the best way but it&#39;s worked =
for us. As for the
maximum number of seeds, we haven&#39;t really used this mod=
ule with more
than a few thousand I&#39;m afraid.



Roger







